sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Gateway
    participant Auth as Auth Middleware<br/>Bearer Token (SHA256)
    participant API as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant Input as InputProcessor<br/>Tokenizer
    participant Engine as EngineCore<br/>Scheduler + KV Cache
    participant Runner as CPU Model Runner<br/>PyTorch CPU
    participant Output as OutputProcessor<br/>Detokenizer
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant OTLP as OTLP Collector<br/>gRPC/HTTP

    Note over Client,OTLP: Flow 1: Inference Request Processing

    Client->>API: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP(S) 8000/TCP<br/>Configurable TLS
    API->>Auth: Validate Bearer Token<br/>SHA256 hash, constant-time compare
    Auth-->>API: 200 OK / 401 Unauthorized
    API->>Input: Process request
    Input->>Input: Tokenize input text<br/>(HuggingFace tokenizers)
    Input->>Engine: Submit tokens + params
    Engine->>Engine: Schedule request<br/>KV cache allocation<br/>Continuous batching
    Engine->>Runner: Execute model forward pass
    Runner->>Runner: PyTorch CPU inference<br/>NUMA-aware, OMP pinned
    Runner-->>Engine: Logits / output tokens
    Engine->>Output: Process output tokens
    Output->>Output: Incremental detokenization
    Output-->>API: Streaming SSE chunks / JSON
    API-->>Client: Response (SSE stream or JSON)

    Note over Client,OTLP: Flow 2: Model Loading (Startup)

    API->>HF: GET model config<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer HF_TOKEN
    HF-->>API: Model config JSON
    API->>HF: GET model weights<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer HF_TOKEN
    HF-->>API: SafeTensors / PyTorch weights
    API->>Runner: Load parameters to CPU memory
    Runner->>Runner: Initialize tensors<br/>Architecture-specific optimizations

    Note over Client,OTLP: Flow 3: Observability

    Prom->>API: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP<br/>Configurable TLS
    API-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>(prometheus_client)
    API->>OTLP: Export traces<br/>gRPC (insecure default)<br/>OpenTelemetry SDK
